BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prohelvetia-fast-forward-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T220812Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Fast Forward (Music)
DESCRIPTION:Fast Forward is a two-year Pro Helvetia programme offering ment
 oring\, management support\, and content-creation funding to help mid-care
 er musicians build international careers\, spanning pop\, rock\, jazz\, el
 ectronic\, experimental\, global sounds\, and hip-hop. Applicants must be 
 mid-career music professionals established in Switzerland's music scene wi
 th regular presence across language regions. ELIGIBILITY: requires a conne
 ction to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, or permanent residency with regu
 lar artistic activity in Switzerland)\; not open to practitioners without 
 a Swiss connection. AMOUNT: CHF 25\,000 per year (maximum CHF 5\,000 for m
 entoring and CHF 10\,000 for musician fees). Submission deadline 1 Septemb
 er (23:59 CEST). Apply via the Pro Helvetia portal.\n\nOrganisation: Pro H
 elvetia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Mid-career musicians established i
 n Switzerland's music scene.\nAward: CHF 25\,000 per year (maximum CHF 5\,
 000 mentoring\; maximum CHF 10\,000 musician fees). No application fee.\nD
 uration: Two-year career-development programme\; deadline 1 September.\n\n
 More: https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/fast-forward?utm_source=artif
 icialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/fast-forward?utm_source=artifici
 alnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Mid-career musicians established in Switzerland's music scene.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prohelvetia-feat-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T220812Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Feat. (Hip-Hop and Clubbing)
DESCRIPTION:Feat. is a Pro Helvetia grant supporting first-time collaborati
 ve projects between hip-hop and/or clubbing artists to produce a joint rel
 ease. Open to DJs\, beatmakers\, rappers\, and producers with at least one
  prior EP or album on a recognized label. Applicants must have a verifiabl
 e connection to Switzerland (citizenship\, permanent residency\, or an ins
 titutional base with regular artistic activity). AMOUNT: up to CHF 10\,000
 . Deadlines twice a year: 1 March (23:59 CET) and 1 September (23:59 CEST)
 . Apply via the Pro Helvetia portal.\n\nOrganisation: Pro Helvetia (Swiss 
 Arts Council)\nLocation: Switzerland-based hip-hop and clubbing artists (D
 Js\, beatmakers\, rappers\, producers).\nAward: Up to CHF 10\,000. No appl
 ication fee.\nDuration: First-time collaborative project resulting in a jo
 int release\; deadlines twice yearly (1 March and 1 September).\n\nMore: h
 ttps://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/feat?utm_source=artificialnouveaugra
 ntdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/feat?utm_source=artificialnouvea
 ugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Switzerland-based hip-hop and clubbing artists (DJs\, beatmakers\,
  rappers\, producers).
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prohelvetia-creation-production-pop-jazz-global-2026@artificialnouveau.
 github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T220812Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Creation and Production: Pop\, Jazz\, Global (Music)
DESCRIPTION:Pro Helvetia's creation and production grant for pop\, jazz\, a
 nd global music supports the creation and production of new musical works 
 (repertoire\, recordings\, performances) by established artists working in
  pop\, rock\, jazz\, electronic\, experimental\, global\, and hip-hop styl
 es. Applicants must be nationally established music professionals or bands
 . ELIGIBILITY: requires a connection to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, o
 r permanent residency with regular artistic activity in Switzerland)\; not
  open to practitioners without a Swiss connection. AMOUNT: maximum CHF 25\
 ,000. Deadlines twice a year: 1 March (23:59 CET) and 1 September (23:59 C
 EST). Apply via the Pro Helvetia portal.\n\nOrganisation: Pro Helvetia (Sw
 iss Arts Council)\nLocation: Nationally established Switzerland-based musi
 c professionals and bands.\nAward: Maximum CHF 25\,000. No application fee
 .\nDuration: Creation/production of new musical works\; deadlines twice ye
 arly (1 March and 1 September).\n\nMore: https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-su
 pport/creation-and-production-pop-jazz-global?utm_source=artificialnouveau
 grantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/creation-and-production-pop-jazz
 -global?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Nationally established Switzerland-based music professionals and b
 ands.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prohelvetia-new-production-performing-arts-2026@artificialnouveau.githu
 b.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T220812Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: New Production (Performing Arts)
DESCRIPTION:Pro Helvetia's new production grant funds new performing arts p
 roductions\, including digital and hybrid formats\, by Switzerland-based a
 rtists and companies with confirmed venue bookings and co-financing in pla
 ce. Open to Swiss citizens\, permanent residents active in Switzerland\, o
 r independent groups and cultural institutions based in Switzerland. ELIGI
 BILITY: requires a connection to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, or perma
 nent residency with regular artistic activity in Switzerland)\; not open t
 o practitioners without a Swiss connection. The grant amount is not specif
 ied on the call page and depends on the project. Deadlines twice a year: 1
  March (23:59 CET) and 1 September (23:59 CEST). Apply via the Pro Helveti
 a portal.\n\nOrganisation: Pro Helvetia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Sw
 itzerland-based independent performing arts companies and artists.\nAward:
  Amount not specified on the call page. No application fee.\nDuration: New
  performing arts production with confirmed venue bookings and co-financing
 \; deadlines twice yearly (1 March and 1 September).\n\nMore: https://proh
 elvetia.ch/en/find-support/new-production?utm_source=artificialnouveaugran
 tdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/new-production?utm_source=artifi
 cialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Switzerland-based independent performing arts companies and artist
 s.
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
UID:prohelvetia-focus-photo-2026@artificialnouveau.github.io
DTSTAMP:20260720T220812Z
DTSTART;VALUE=DATE:20260901
DTEND;VALUE=DATE:20260902
SUMMARY:Deadline: Focus Photo (Visual Arts)
DESCRIPTION:Focus Photo is a Pro Helvetia grant supporting new artistic\, d
 ocumentary\, or applied photography projects\, whether analogue\, digital\
 , or post-photographic. Open to Swiss citizens\, permanent residents activ
 e in Switzerland\, or Swiss-based groups and institutions. ELIGIBILITY: re
 quires a connection to Switzerland (Swiss citizenship\, or permanent resid
 ency with regular artistic activity in Switzerland)\; not open to practiti
 oners without a Swiss connection. AMOUNT: maximum CHF 25\,000. Submission 
 deadline 1 September (23:59 CEST). Apply via the Pro Helvetia portal.\n\nO
 rganisation: Pro Helvetia (Swiss Arts Council)\nLocation: Switzerland-base
 d photographers and collectives.\nAward: Maximum CHF 25\,000. No applicati
 on fee.\nDuration: New photography project (artistic\, documentary\, or ap
 plied)\; deadline 1 September.\n\nMore: https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-sup
 port/focus-photo?utm_source=artificialnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
URL:https://prohelvetia.ch/en/find-support/focus-photo?utm_source=artificia
 lnouveaugrantdesk&utm_medium=referral
LOCATION:Switzerland-based photographers and collectives.
END:VEVENT
